item.title: [HBASE-11593] TestCacheConfig failing consistently in precommit builds
item.summary: TestCacheConfig failing consistently in precommit builds

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.

comments.comment: I'm on this one. It is my test. Keeping block cache instance in static global for test sake seems to be messing us up. Undoing it...

One precommit build log where this test failed shows the kernel version as:

Linux asf901 3.13.0-24-generic #47-Ubuntu SMP Fri May 2 23:30:00 UTC 2014 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux

and the Java version as:

java version "1.7.0_51"

Java(TM) SE Runtime Environment (build 1.7.0_51-b13)

Java HotSpot(TM) 64-Bit Server VM (build 24.51-b03, mixed mode)

I ran TestCacheConfig in a loop 10 times locally on an Ubuntu system with kernel 3.13.0-29-generic #53-Ubuntu and 64-bit Java 7u51 and 7u60. It passed every time.

Thanks Andrew Purtell I've been watching it and can't repro locally. My guess is that issue is that it is a small test and all small tests run in the one jvm in // and are interfering with each other since blockcache is in static (for tests).

Removes static globals used hosting block cache instances. Let me see what it breaks.

Patch is a little large because had to do cleanup in a few tests where cache settings are being done against global cache and then a local cache and it all gets hard to follow which cache is expected where.

Also set size bounds on the TestMapPool tests. Could be any size and OOME'd (might because we are retaining BlockCache instances.... will see)
